  "texts": [
    "Specifically, f s t ∈ R 1ÂC represents the feature vector of a specific disease area in the image.",
    "The default value for C is 1,024.",
    "The structure of the sequence encoding module is shown in area ② in Figure 6.",
    "The intermediate variable of the function μ a in the region detection module is used as input to the sequence encoding module, where the intermediate variable is essentially the visual vector generated by the integration of all disease regions in the image.",
    "This collection of visual vectors is referred to as the visual vector sequence, denoted as F s = f s 1, f s 2,:::, f s t f g, where F s ∈ R tÂC."
